en.name: Bofors Ak5C 5.56x45 assault rifle
en.description: The Ak5C is the modernized version of the original Ak 5, the Swedish version of the Belgian FN FNC assault rifle. Manufactured under license from FN by Saab Bofors Dynamics for the Swedish military, it fires at a cyclic rate of 650 rpm and has low recoil. It uses the standard 5.56x45mm NATO round.

en.description: The Bofors Ak5C RIS (Rail Interface System) is the standard handguard issued with the Ak5C; it was designed to allow the mounting of a front foregrip and tactical devices to aide the user. Manufactured by Bofors Carl Gustav.

en.name: Bofors Ak5D 5.56x45 assault rifle
en.description: The Ak5D is the shortened, modernized version of the original Ak 5, the Swedish version of the Belgian FN FNC assault rifle. Manufactured under license from FN by Saab Bofors Dynamics for the Swedish military, it fires at a cyclic rate of 650 rpm and has low recoil. It uses the standard 5.56x45mm NATO round.

en.name: Bofors Ak5G 5.56x45 light machinegun
en.description: The Ak5G is the light machinegun variant of the Ak5C 5.56x45 rifle.  The Ak5G variant is equipped with a heavier barrel and metal handguard with heatshield.
